headline: Planned turnaround ongoing at Phillips 66's Wood River refinery, IIR says
summary: Phillips 66's 356,500 barrel-per-day Wood River refinery is undergoing a turnaround, research company IIR Energy said on Thursday. The refinery, in Roxana, Illinois, began maintenance activities last week, IIR said. Ongoing maintenance work at the refinery's 170,000-bpd crude distillation unit, 50,000-bpd vacuum flasher, 42,000-bpd catalytic cracker unit, and associated gas plant units is expected to continue until April.
